e created during the series:\r\n\r\n[page_actions]<a href=\"http://ajesuschurch.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/ajc_mark_timeline.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Timeline of Mark Infographic</a> [/page_actions] [page_actions]<a href=\"http://ajesuschurch.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/ajc_mark_bookmark.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Recommended Reading Bookmark</a> [/page_actions] [page_actions]<a href=\"http://ajesuschurch.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/ajc_mark_galilee_map.jpg\" target=\"_blank\">Region of Galilee Map</a> [/page_actions] [page_actions]<a href=\"http://ajesuschurch.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/ajc_mark_herodincest.jpg\" target=\"_blank\">The Incest of Herod Infographic</a> [/page_actions]','no'),(670,'_teaching_series_10_content','field_53911b9fbc546','no'),(672,'teaching_series_8_content','In the beginning God created man and woman, and ever since we have been asking questions about love, marriage, sex, and romance. Loveology is an exploration of what the Bible has to say about the never ending story of male and female.\r\n\r\nBased on the writing of the book, the Loveology Series features in-depth discussion from lead pastor and author John Mark Comer, guest teachers, and a live Q&amp;A session\r\n\r\nLoveology the book is available on Amazon.\r\n\r\n[page_actions]<a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Loveology-Love-Marriage-never-ending-female/dp/1491501340\" target=\"_blank\">Purchase Loveology</a> [/page_actions]','no'),(673,'_teaching_series_8_content','field_53911b9fbc546','no'),(675,'teaching_series_16_content','There’s something in us as humans that knows things should be different. When we see injustice, when children three or four years old wander the streets begging for money to survive, with no parents, all alone; when the AIDS pandemic sweeps away millions of lives; when disparity separates the rich and the poor; when the opulent waste of American culture sits next to the 3 billion people who live on less than two dollars a day, something in us says, that’s not right.\r\n\r\nAt the Bridgetown: A Jesus Church, 10% of every dollar goes directly to Hear the Cry; a work for the widow, the orphan and the poor. Our church identity is found in our dedication to justice and generosity. We want to bring the kingdom of God to Earth and see the hearts of men and women filled with shalom.','no'),(676,'_teaching_series_16_content','field_53911b9fbc546','no'),(678,'teaching_series_14_content','Who is God? Is God a he, a she, a they, or an it? Is God a force or a person? Is God good or evil? Strong or weak? Close or far away? What is God like?\r\n\r\nThe fact is that everyone has a picture of God, whether right or wrong. However, to answer the question of who God is, we have to go to the source.\r\n\r\nExodus 34v6-7, is God\'s self-disclosure of Himself. It is the only place in all of the Bible where God describes Himself and because of that, it is the most quoted verse in the Bible, by the Bible, and the epicenter for a theology of God.','no'),(679,'_teaching_series_14_content','field_53911b9fbc546','no'),(688,'teaching_series_17_content','<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Acts 16 tells the story of Paul coming to plant a church in Philippi, a colony of Rome. Living under the impression of Roman culture and rule as a colony, Paul commissions the people to live out the gospel--finding joy in the middle of suffering as \"a colony of heaven.\"</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Just as Paul encouraged the Philippians, we too are encouraged to live out the gospel. Working in and through the church as a community, formed in partnership around the gospel, in humility and unity.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">The Philippians series focuses on nine themes: the gospel, the church, partnership around the gospel, humility, unity, the colony, following Jesus, suffering for the gospel, and joy.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"color: #525252;\">These resources were created during the series:</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">[page_actions]<a href=\"http://ajesuschurch.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/ajc_philippians_bookmark.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Recommended Reading Bookmark</a> [/page_actions]</p>','no'),(689,'_teaching_series_17_content','field_53911b9fbc546','no'),(690,'teaching_series_17_poster_image','857','no'),(691,'_teaching_series_17_poster_image','field_5371d964bcccf','no'),(692,'teaching_series_17_foreground','white','no'),(693,'_teaching_series_17_foreground','field_53845d1e64fa9','no'),(793,'pb_backupbuddy','a:72:{s:12:\"data_version\";s:1:\"8\";s:21:\"importbuddy_pass_hash\";s:0:\"\";s:23:\"importbuddy_pass_length\";i:0;s:16:\"backup_reminders\";i:1;s:16:\"edits_since_last\";i:2759;s:17:\"last_backup_start\";i:0;s:18:\"last_backup_finish\";i:0;s:18:\"last_backup_serial\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"last_backup_stats\";a:0:{}s:19:\"force_compatibility\";i:0;s:29:\"force_mysqldump_compatibility\";i:0;s:9:\"schedules\";a:0:{}s:9:\"log_level\";s:1:\"1\";s:13:\"high_security\";i:0;s:19:\"next_schedule_index\";i:100;s:13:\"archive_limit\";i:0;s:18:\"archive_limit_size\";i:0;s:17:\"archive_limit_age\";i:0;s:26:\"delete_archives_pre_backup\";i:0;s:23:\"lock_archives_directory\";i:0;s:28:\"email_notify_scheduled_start\";s:0:\"\";s:36:\"email_notify_scheduled_start_subject\";s:49:\"BackupBuddy Scheduled Backup Started - {site_url}\";s:33:\"email_notify_scheduled_start_body\";s:140:\"A scheduled backup has started with BackupBuddy v{backupbuddy_version} on {current_datetime} for the site {site_url}.\n\nDetails:\r\n\r\n{message}\";s:31:\"email_notify_scheduled_complete\";s:0:\"\";s:39:\"email_notify_scheduled_complete_subject\";s:50:\"BackupBuddy Scheduled Backup Complete - {site_url}\";s:36:\"email_notify_scheduled_complete_body\";s:142:\"A scheduled backup has completed with BackupBuddy v{backupbuddy_version} on {current_datetime} for the site {site_url}.\n\nDetails:\r\n\r\n{message}\";s:24:\"email_notify_send_finish\";s:0:\"\";s:32:\"email_notify_send_finish_subject\";s:43:\"BackupB