For years, John Mark Comer thought he was the only man on the planet who struggled with anxiety and depression. The truth is, staggering numbers of modern Americans fight anxiety and depression. In 2010, there were 253 million prescriptions for antidepressants in the U.S. alone--That’s in a nation of 311 million people!</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">The series covers the story of one follower of Jesus who went through the horrors of anxiety and depression and came out the other side. My Name is Hope is his ruthlessly authentic and scripturally authoritative account of prophets and poets, mothers and fathers, and even a Messiah who all came up against anxiety and depression.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Through this experience, John Mark Comer wrote a book to tell the story. <em>My Name Is Hope</em> is available on Amazon.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">[page_actions]<a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Name-Hope-John-Mark-Comer/dp/0615565654\" target=\"_blank\">Purchase My Name Is Hope</a> [/page_actions]</p>','no'),(836,'_teaching_series_21_content','field_53911b9fbc546','no'),(837,'teaching_series_21_poster_image','869','no'),(838,'_teaching_series_21_poster_image','field_5371d964bcccf','no'),(839,'teaching_series_21_foreground','white','no'),(840,'_teaching_series_21_foreground','field_53845d1e64fa9','no'),(842,'teaching_series_22_content','<span style=\"color: #000000;\">Jesus\' most influential, revered and controversial teachings are collected by his biographers in the sermon on the mount. Prayer, adultery, money, divorce, violence, anxiety... all of these things are addressed by Jesus, each of his statements more unexpected, controversial and life-giving than the next. Salt + Light is a study of these teachings, one by one, and what it means for his followers 2,000 years later.</span>','no'),(843,'_teaching_series_22_content','field_53911b9fbc546','no'),(844,'teaching_series_22_poster_image','879','no'),(845,'_teaching_series_22_poster_image','field_5371d964bcccf','no'),(846,'teaching_series_22_foreground','white','no'),(847,'_teaching_series_22_foreground','field_53845d1e64fa9','no'),(863,'teaching_structure','/%teaching_series%/%postname%/','yes'),(864,'no_taxonomy_structure','1','yes'),(866,'remove_taxonomy_base_slug_settings_what_taxonomies','a:1:{i:0;s:8:\"ministry\";}','yes'),(892,'teaching_series_8_tile_image','872','no'),(893,'_teaching_series_8_tile_image','field_5361ca65b45c1','no'),(895,'teaching_series_10_tile_image','841','no'),(896,'_teaching_series_10_tile_image','field_5361ca65b45c1','no'),(899,'teaching_series_16_tile_image','871','no'),(900,'_teaching_series_16_tile_image','field_5361ca65b45c1','no'),(902,'teaching_series_14_tile_image','890','no'),(903,'_teaching_series_14_tile_image','field_5361ca65b45c1','no'),(908,'teaching_series_17_tile_image','856','no'),(909,'_teaching_series_17_tile_image','field_5361ca65b45c1','no'),(911,'teaching_series_20_tile_image','866','no'),(912,'_teaching_series_20_tile_image','field_5361ca65b45c1','no'),(914,'teaching_series_21_tile_image','868','no'),(915,'_teaching_series_21_tile_image','field_5361ca65b45c1','no'),(917,'teaching_series_22_tile_image','878','no'),(918,'_teaching_series_22_tile_image','field_5361ca65b45c1','no'),(920,'teaching_series_19_tile_image','873','no'),(921,'_teaching_series_19_tile_image','field_5361ca65b45c1','no'),(956,'teaching_series_25_content','Each year, Bridgetown Church holds a Vision Series. We take this time to look at where we’ve been as a church, set vision for our next year, and pray as a family. Follow along as we discover what it means to be the family of God, on the mission of God, living as disciples of Jesus. We want to see the Kingdom of God in Portland as it is in Heaven.\r\n\r\nDuring the series we worked through a Missional Community Primer so that new communities could form and current communities would be renewed in their vision. We encourage everybody to work through the primer with their Missional Community.\r\n\r\n[page_actions]<a href=\"http://ajesuschurch.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/ajc_bt_mc_primer.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Missional Community Primer</a> [/page_actions]','no'),(957,'_teaching_series_25_content','field_53911b9fbc546','no'),(958,'teaching_series_25_poster_image','840','no'),(959,'_teaching_series_25_poster_image','field_5371d964bcccf','no'),(960,'teaching_series_25_tile_image','840','no'),(961,'_teaching_series_25_tile_image','field_5361ca65b45c1','no'),(962,'teaching_series_25_foreground','white','no'),(963,'_teaching_series_25_foreground','field_53845d1e64fa9','no'),(1114,'teaching_series_26_content','<span style=\"color: #525252;\">In the church, as a general rule, we often teach people how to read the Scriptures, how to pray, how to repent of sin, have faith, do justice, preach the gospel, etc. But we don’t teach people how to navigate emotional pain. How to feel, and to feel well.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #222222;\">The Emotionally Healthy Church series is designed to reshape our church from the inside out. We want to explore areas that we have never been before in the hopes that we would become more like Jesus.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #222222;\">The following books have been tremendously influential in shaping the series:</span>\r\n\r\n[page_actions] <a href=\"http://ajesuschurch.org/blog/bthealthychurch-reading-list/\">Recommended Reading</a> [/page_actions]','no'),(1115,'_teaching_series_26_content','field_53911b9fbc546','no'),(1116,'teaching_series_26_poster_image','839','no'),(1117,'_teaching_series_26_poster_image','field_5371d964bcccf','no'),(1118,'teaching_series_26_tile_image','885','no'),(1119,'_teaching_series_26_tile_image','field_5361ca65b45c1','no'),(1120,'teaching_series_26_foreground','white','no'),(1121,'_teaching_series_26_foreground','field_53845d1e64fa9','no'),(1177,'teaching_series_27_content','<p style=\"color: #525252;\">Where did it come from? How did it get here? What does my purchase support?</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #525252;\">But it isn’t with complete ignorance that we forego a peek behind the curtain. We’ve heard about injustice in the labor industry: stories about sweatshops in which children are forced to work grueling hours in deplorable conditions under the awful mastery of slave drivers. Factories that collapse and kill hundreds. Women that are trafficked into slavery in front of a sewing machine.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #525252;\">But we’ve heard other things as well. “This company is bad, that company is good.” “It’s not as bad as it sounds.” “It’s better than no job at all.” “The industry is inherently flawed. No one can shop without <em>some </em>blood on their hands.”</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #525252;\">For those of us that are disciples of Jesus of Nazareth, <em>the</em> fundamental precept of our apprenticeship to Jesus is that we live out the way of Jesus. That we learn his teachings, that we make the way he thinks and sees the way that we think and see. That we become like Jesus. That we carry on his work in the world.</p>','no'),(1178,'_teaching_series_27_content','field_53911b9fbc546','no'),(1179,'teaching_series_27_poster_image','1377','no'),(1180,'_teaching_series_27_poster_image','field_5371d964bcccf','no'),(1181,'teaching_series_27_tile_image','1378','no'),(1182,'_teaching_series_27_tile_image','field_5361ca65b45c1','no'),(1183,'teaching_series_27_foreground','white','no'),(1184,'_teaching_series_27_foreground','field_53845d1e64fa9','no'),(1363,'teaching_series_28_content','<span style=\"color: #222222;\">For us, this is more than a series, this is the next step forward in our journey as a church. For years we\'ve been wanting to see and know more of the Spirit. Now it\'s time to dive in head first. Follow along as we discover the Holy Spirit.</span>\r\n<p style=\"color: #323333;\">This series will focus on a comprehensive biblical theology of the Holy Spirit, centered around the “manifestations” of 1 Corinthians, specifically prophecy and healing. Our goal is to discover how to operate in the Spirit and build out a culture of Holy Spirit empowerment at Bridgetown.</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"color: #222222;\">\r\n\r\nThe following books have been tremendously influential in shaping the series:\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[page_actions]<a href=\"http://ajesuschurch.org/blog/receive-the-holy-spirit-recommended-reading/\"> Recommended Reading</a> [/page_actions]','no'),(1364,'_teaching_series_28_content','field_53911b9fbc546','no'),(1365,'teaching_series_28_poster_image','1043','no'),(1366,'_teaching_series_28_poster_image','field_5371d964bcccf','no'),(1367,'teaching_series_28_tile_image','1042','no'),(1368,'_teaching_series_28_tile_image','field_5361ca65b45c1','no'),(1369,'teaching_series_28_foreground','white','no'),(1370,'_teaching_series_28_foreground','field_53845d1e64fa9','no'),(1401,'ministry_29_content','<span style=\"color: #222222;\">At Bridgetown, we want to see high school students understand who they are in Christ, and that their lives have a purpose in the Kingdom of God. We want to invest into the next generation of Jesus followers. Look forward to new events and trips coming each year. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h1>Sunday Gatherings</h1>\r\n<div style=\"color: #222222;\">[two_third padding=\"0 25px 0 0\"]Each week we gather from all over the city as high schoolers to <span style=\"color: #525252;\">learn the Scriptures, pray for one another, create space to hear from the Spirit.</span> and spend time together. Come hang out with us and enjoy good company. Youth Room is located at the end of the hall, past the Chapel.</div>\r\n<div style=\"color: #222222;\">[/two_third][one_third_last]</div>\r\n<div style=\"color: #222222;\">\r\n<div><strong>Dates:</strong> Sundays</div>\r\n<div><strong>Time: </strong>3:30 – 5 PM</div>\r\n<div><strong>Location:</strong> First Baptist Church, Youth Room</div>\r\n<div>[/one_third_last]</div>\r\n<div>[page_actions][email address=<span style=\"color: #555555;\">alexrettmann@ajesuschurch.org</span>]Contact For More Information[/email][/page_actions]</div>\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />','no'),(1402,'_ministry_29_content','field_53900b9fae549','no'),(1403,'ministry_29_events_heading','Events','no'),(1404,'_ministry_29_events_heading','field_537ac1a185840','no'),(1405,'ministry_29_tile_image','893','no'),(1406,'_ministry_29_tile_image','field_539949c5a6b52','no'),(1407,'ministry_29_foreground','white','no'),(1408,'_ministry_29_foreground','field_537f17c949914','no'),(1409,'ministry_29_vibe_banner','','no'),(1410,'_ministry_29_vibe_banner','field_535d47ac31b0e','no'),(1411,'ministry_29_hero_graphic','1209','no'),(1412,'_ministry_29_hero_graphic','field_535d48d19a78d','no'),(1413,'ministry_29_hero_phrase','High School','no'),(1414,'_ministry_29_hero_phrase','field_535f146b1c2b1','no'),(1415,'ministry_29_hero_font_size','','no'),(1416,'_ministry_29_hero_font_size','field_53adff30a79d5','no'),(1417,'ministry_29_vimeo_id','','no'),(1418,'_ministry_29_vimeo_id','field_535d4fb339065','no'),(1419,'ministry_29_watch_button_text','','no'),(1420,'_ministry_29_watch_button_text','field_5390e9649db12','no'),(1421,'ministry_29_darken_header','1','no'),(1422,'_ministry_29_darken_header','field_539917531c248','no'),(1649,'teaching_series_30_content','A series through the first letter to the Corinthians.','no'),(1650,'_teaching_series_30_content','field_53911b9fbc546','no'),(1651,'teaching_series_30_poster_image','907','no'),(1652,'_teaching_series_30_poster_image','field_5371d964bcccf','no'),(1653,'teaching_series_30_tile_image','910','no'),(1654,'_teaching_series_30_tile_image','field_5361ca65b45c1','no'),(1655,'teaching_series_30_foreground','white','no'),(1656,'_teaching_series_30_foreground','field_53845d1e64fa9','no'),(2013,'teaching_series_32_content','<p style=\"color: #141823;\">In this age of perpetual conflict and despair the future often looks dark. For millennia, humankind has been caught in the struggle between good and evil. As followers of Jesus, we press through the difficulties because there is a promise for the future.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #141823;\">God has a plan to rebuild creation and put the world to rights. The Kingdom of God will soon become fully realized, and we must live as <span class=\"text_exposed_show\">an advanced sign of the world to come. Followers of Jesus must be the archetypes of a new humanity.</span></p>','no'),(2014,'_teaching_series_32_content','field_53911b9fbc546','no'),(2015,'teaching_series_32_poster_image','1050','no'),(2016,'_teaching_series_32_poster_image','field_5371d964bcccf','no'),(2017,'teaching_series_32_tile_image','1038','no'),(2018,'_teaching_series_32_tile_image','field_5361ca65b45c1','no'),(2019,'teaching_series_32_foreground','white','no'),(2020,'_teaching_series_32_foreground','field_53845d1e64fa9','no'),(2485,'teaching_series_34_content','<span style=\"color: #525252;\">Each year, Bridgetown Church creates space to look at where we’ve been as a church, set vision for the next year, and pray as a family. T</span>his is a time to refocus as the family of God, on the mission of God, living as disciples of Jesus. Listen to the Vision Series as we discover what it means to be the people of God in a place.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #525252;\">During the series we work through a Missional Community Commitment so that communities can renew their vision. We encourage everybody to work through the commitment with their Missional Community.</span>\r\n\r\n[page_actions]<a href=\"http://ajesuschurch.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/ajc_bt_mc_2015-2016_commitment.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Missional Community Commitment</a>[/page_actions]','no'),(2486,'_teaching_series_34_content','field_53911b9fbc546','no'),(2487,'teaching_series_34_poster_image','1293','no'),(2488,'_teaching_series_34_poster_image','field_5371d964bcccf','no'),(2489,'teaching_series_34_tile_image','1293','no'),(2490,'_teaching_series_34_tile_image','field_5361ca65b45c1','no'),(2491,'teaching_series_34_foreground','white','no'),(2492,'_teaching_series_34_foreground','field_53845d1e64fa9','no'),(2673,'teaching_series_36_content','<div style=\"color: #222222;\">From the first page of the bible forward, human beings were made to rule over the earth, to gather up the raw materials of the planet, and carve out a world. Out of this inherent design, we search for our calling in life and find meaning in the normal, ordinary stuff of life like going to work, writing emails, cleaning the house, raising kids, and doing homework.</div>\r\n<span style=\"color: #222222;\">During this series, we will take a look at Genesis and the story of a man, a woman, and a garden as we ask the ancient question, \"What does it mean to be human?\" Listen to the Garden City teaching series as we discover God\'s design for work, rest, and being human.</span>\r\n\r\n<strong>Sabbath Curriculum:</strong> Follow along with our Five Week Curriculum on how to Sabbath.\r\n\r\n[page_actions]<a href=\"http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2015/12/sabbath.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Sabbath Curriculum</a>[/page_actions]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #525252;\">The following books have been tremendously influential in shaping the series. </span>\r\n\r\n[page_actions]<a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Garden-City-Work-Being-Human/dp/0310337313\" target=\"_blank\">Garden City Book</a> <a href=\"http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/blog/garden-city-recommended-reading/\">Other Recommended Reading</a>[/page_actions]','no'),(2674,'_teaching_series_36_content','field_53911b9fbc546','no'),(2675,'teaching_series_36_poster_image','1379','no'),(2676,'_teaching_series_36_poster_image','field_5371d964bcccf','no'),(2677,'teaching_series_36_tile_image','1380','no'),(2678,'_teaching_series_36_tile_image','field_5361ca65b45c1','no'),(2679,'teaching_series_36_foreground','white','no'),(2680,'_teaching_series_36_foreground','field_53845d1e64fa9','no'),(2806,'page_for_posts','2452','yes'),(2891,'teaching_series_39_content','We have a problem with the Bible. More and more followers of Jesus in the west don’t read it, don’t now <i>how </i>to read it, don’t even like it, and frankly, take issue with it. So why do we follow the Bible? Because we follow Jesus. He is our authority, but he has mediated his authority <i>through </i>the Bible. And on its pages we discover the map to the life that Jesus has on offer.\r\n\r\nThis series is part of the Year of Biblical Literacy. Participate with us and discover the relevance of the Bible to our modern society.\r\n\r\n[page_actions]<a href=\"http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/bible\">Year of Biblical Literacy</a>[/page_actions]','no'),(2892,'_teaching_series_39_content','field_53911b9fbc546','no'),(2893,'teaching_series_39_poster_image','1843','no'),(2894,'_teaching_series_39_poster_image','field_5371d964bcccf','no'),(2895,'teaching_series_39_tile_image','2033','no'),(2896,'_teaching_series_39_tile_image','field_5361ca65b45c1','no'),(2897,'teaching_series_39_foreground','white','no'),(2898,'_teaching_series_39_foreground','field_53845d1e64fa9','no'),(2947,'teaching_series_41_content','','no'),(2948,'_teaching_series_41_content','field_53911b9fbc546','no'),(2949,'teaching_series_41_poster_image','1856','no'),(2950,'_teaching_series_41_poster_image','field_5371d964bcccf','no'),(2951,'teaching_series_41_tile_image','1855','no'),(2952,'_teaching_series_41_tile_image','field_5361ca65b45c1','no'),(2953,'teaching_series_41_foreground','white','no'),(2954,'_teaching_series_41_foreground','field_53845d1e64fa9','no'),(3065,'teaching_series_44_content','The Bible is a story. A single, unified story about God, humanity, and the world that points its readers to Jesus. As disciples of Jesus, we work to understand what the Bible communicates within the context of this great story. To do that, we must know and understand the story itself. Listen along as we explore the meta-narrative, or the overall story arc of the Bible.\r\n<p style=\"color: #525252;\">This series is part of the Year of Biblical Literacy.</p>\r\n[page_actions]<a href=\"http://bridgetownajc.org/bible\">Year of Biblical Literacy</a>[/page_actions]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','no'),(3066,'_teaching_series_44_content','field_53911b9fbc546','no'),(3067,'teaching_series_44_poster_image','2031','no'),(3068,'_teaching_series_44_poster_image','field_5371d964bcccf','no'),(3069,'teaching_series_44_tile_image','2038','no'),(3070,'_teaching_series_44_tile_image','field_5361ca65b45c1','no'),(3071,'teaching_series_44_foreground','white','no'),(3072,'_teaching_series_44_foreground','field_53845d1e64fa9','no'),(3270,'teaching_series_45_content','The story of Israel is a long and often confusing account of God\'s interaction with humankind. Israel is perpetually disobeying God, suffering the consequences, and repenting of their sin. In this story, there are many occasions of violence, brutality, sacrifice, and sexuality that are difficult to reconcile with the teachings of Jesus. So it forces us to ask, is this story relevant to modern society? Gather with us as we work through The Story of Israel.\r\n\r\nThis series is part of the Year of Biblical Literacy.\r\n\r\n[page_actions]<a href=\"http://bridgetownajc.org/bible\">Year of Biblical Literacy</a>[/page_actions]','no'),(3271,'_teaching_series_45_content','field_53911b9fbc546','no'),(3272,'teaching_series_45_poster_image','2206','no'),(3273,'_teaching_series_45_poster_image','field_5371d964bcccf','no'),(3274,'teaching_series_45_tile_image','2207','no'),(3275,'_teaching_series_45_tile_image','field_5361ca65b45c1','no'),(3276,'teaching_series_45_foreground','white','no'),(3277,'_teaching_series_45_foreground','field_53845d1e64fa9','no'),(3454,'teaching_series_46_content','Who are the Prophets and what are they about? Covenant watchdogs, accusers of social injustice, announcers of God\'s authority, messengers of the future mercy and salvation—who are these individuals through whom God has chosen to 