INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (4,1,'2014-03-06 06:27:35','2014-03-06 06:27:35','<h1>About Bridgetown</h1>\r\nLocated in Portland, Oregon we are a church for the city. We want to see God’s will done in Portland as it is in Heaven. [page_actions]<a href=\"http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/about/\">More About Bridgetown</a> [/page_actions]','Home','','publish','closed','closed','','home','','','2016-07-27 08:57:57','2016-07-27 16:57:57','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?page_id=4',0,'page','',0),(8,1,'2014-04-16 04:56:36','2014-04-16 04:56:36','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Suspendisse imperdiet luctus dapibus. Sed aliquam sagittis sagittis. Fusce malesuada risus vitae feugiat placerat. Ut egestas turpis quis arcu egestas, vel venenatis dui condimentum. Pellentesque porttitor eget eros nec blandit. <a href=\"http://something\" target=\"_blank\">Nulla lorem purus</a>, scelerisque id sollicitudin nec, molestie eget ligula. Pellentesque sed arcu blandit, tempus magna eget, blandit dui. Morbi at lacinia sapien, vel sollicitudin justo. Interdum et malesuada fames ac ante ipsum primis in faucibus.','Teaching','','publish','closed','closed','','teaching','','','2016-07-07 22:45:34','2016-07-08 06:45:34','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?page_id=8',0,'page','',0),(9,1,'2014-04-16 04:56:53','2014-04-16 04:56:53','<h1>More Gatherings</h1>\r\nAs a church that values loving God with our hearts, <em>and with our minds</em>, we also gather in the House of Learning and Basics classes. Throughout the week we gather as brothers and sisters in similar stages of life and age groups to grow together in our discipleship to Jesus.','Gather','','publish','closed','closed','','gather','','','2016-04-27 15:32:43','2016-04-27 23:32:43','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?page_id=9',0,'page','',0),(10,1,'2014-04-16 04:57:08','2014-04-16 04:57:08','<h2>How We Scatter</h2>\r\n<div class=\"embed-container\"><style>.embed-container { position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden; max-width: 100%; } .embed-container iframe, .embed-container object, .embed-container embed { position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; }</style><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/160501926\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></div>\r\nDuring the week we “scatter” in neighborhoods across the urban core of Portland to live out the teachings of Jesus. The primary way this happens is in Missional Communities. We also work for justice both globally and locally through Hear the Cry—an initiative funded by ten percent of all giving that comes into the church. Another ten percent goes directly to planting new churches from scratch, helping established churches grow, and furthering evangelism.\r\n<h2>Missional Communities</h2>\r\nThe primary way we scatter is through Missional Communities, which we define as “a family of missionary disciples”. It’s where we live as brothers and sisters, eating, praying, and doing life together. It’s also where we live as “missionaries” as we join in Jesus’ kingdom work in our neighborhoods, workplaces, and city. And finally it’s where we grow in our discipleship to Jesus himself.\r\n\r\n[page_actions]<a href=\"/basics\">Sign up for a basics class</a> [email address=bridgetownmc@ajesuschurch.org]Get more information[/email][/page_actions]','Scatter','','publish','closed','closed','','scatter','','','2016-07-08 00:04:26','2016-07-08 08:04:26','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?page_id=10',0,'page','',0),(11,1,'2014-04-16 04:57:27','2014-04-16 04:57:27','<h1>Serve with Bridgetown</h1>\r\nFollowers of Jesus are called to become servants. We want to actively demonstrate self-sacrificial love by serving those both in and outside the church. It takes hundreds of volunteers to pull off the many gatherings taking place each week. We are a family, and like a family, we all pitch in.\r\n\r\n[page_actions]<a href=\"http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/serve/register\">Register to Serve</a> [/page_actions]','Serve','','publish','closed','closed','','serve','','','2016-05-24 16:10:57','2016-05-25 00:10:57','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?page_id=11',0,'page','',0),(12,1,'2014-04-16 05:02:03','2014-04-16 05:02:03',' ','','','publish','open','closed','','12','','','2016-07-26 17:16:43','2016-07-27 01:16:43','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?p=12',4,'nav_menu_item','',0),(13,1,'2014-04-16 05:02:03','2014-04-16 05:02:03',' ','','','publish','open','closed','','13','','','2016-07-26 17:16:43','2016-07-27 01:16:43','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?p=13',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),(14,1,'2014-04-16 05:02:03','2014-04-16 05:02:03',' ','','','publish','open','closed','','14','','','2016-07-26 17:16:43','2016-07-27 01:16:43','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?p=14',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(15,1,'2014-04-16 05:02:03','2014-04-16 05:02:03',' ','','','publish','open','closed','','15','','','2016-07-26 17:16:43','2016-07-27 01:16:43','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?p=15',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(17,1,'2014-04-16 05:02:39','2014-04-16 05:02:39','<h1>Bridgetown Church Giving</h1>\r\n[page_actions]<a href=\"https://pushpay.com/pay/bridgetown\" target=\"_blank\">Give To Bridgetown Church</a>[/page_actions]\r\n\r\nWith Bridgetown Church we want to partner with Jesus to serve our city. <span style=\"color: #525252;\">We dream of becoming a church marked by radical generosity. </span><span style=\"color: #525252;\">Ten percent</span> of every dollar goes directly to supporting <a href=\"http://ajesuschurch.org/justice\" target=\"_blank\">justice work</a> both globally and locally.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h1>2015 Annual Report</h1>\r\n<span style=\"color: #303030;\">Our A</span><span class=\"il\" style=\"color: #303030;\">nnual</span><span style=\"color: #303030;\"> R</span><span class=\"il\" style=\"color: #303030;\">eport</span><span style=\"color: #303030;\"> is an opportunity to look back and celebrate God’s faithfulness. These numbers and stories reveal what we have been up to, how we are spending God’s money, and help us set goals for the future.</span>\r\n\r\n[page_actions]<a href=\"http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2016/01/ajc_bt_annualreport_2015.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">2015 Annual Report (PDF)</a>[/page_actions]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"color: #222222;\">Manage Your Account</h2>\r\nWith Pushpay you can login at any time to view your giving history, make changes to your account, and update credit card information. Our recent transition to Pushpay means that we will no longer be using GivingFuel for church giving. If you have established recurring giving through GivingFuel please cancel your scheduled giving and reestablish with Pushpay.\r\n\r\n[page_actions]<a href=\"https://pushpay.com/login\" target=\"_blank\">Login to Pushpay</a> <a href=\"https://ajesuschurchfamily.webconnex.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Login to GivingFuel</a>[/page_actions]','Give','','publish','closed','closed','','give','','','2016-05-01 13:35:19','2016-05-01 21:35:19','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?page_id=17',0,'page','',0),(18,1,'2014-04-16 05:08:28','2014-04-16 05:08:28',' ','','','publish','open','closed','','18','','','2016-07-26 17:16:43','2016-07-27 01:16:43','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?p=18',5,'nav_menu_item','',0),(23,1,'2014-04-25 22:40:01','2014-04-25 22:40:01','<h1>Learning at Bridgetown</h1>\r\nWe believe God wants us to love him not only with our hearts, souls, and strength, but with our minds as well. We offer several ways to learn outside of the normal weekend gatherings. “Basics” introduces people to Bridgetown’s history, theological distinctives, and Missional Communities. The House of Learning offers weekly, seminary-style classes focused on equipping followers of Jesus to better understand biblical studies, theology, and doctrine on their own.\r\n<h2>Lead</h2>\r\nLead is a cohort-based leadership development initiative. Its purpose is to train men and women by encouraging and facilitating collective growth in the home, school, workplace, and church. Each cohort is led by a pastor, elder, deacon, or other qualified vocation-focused leader and is shape around different areas of engagement in the church and culture. Lead members will spend nine months in their cohorts, reading, serving, and learning together. Cohorts are assembled by leaders based on existing relationships and a demonstrated commitment to helping the Family of God grow.\r\n<h2>Bible Reading Plan</h2>\r\nWe believe the Scriptures are inspired and authoritative. The Bible is not a rulebook. It’s more than principles for a better life. It’s better than simply a manifesto for the Kingdom of God. The Bible is a story — the meta-narrative of God’s redemptive work in creation. We want to know the Bible well. Each year we encourage people to use this Bible reading outline and journey through the entirety of the Scriptures together.\r\n\r\n[page_actions]<a href=\"http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/bible/read\" target=\"_blank\">Bible Reading Plan</a>[/page_actions]','Learning','','publish','closed','closed','','learning','','','2016-01-27 15:53:24','2016-01-27 23:53:24','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?page_id=23',0,'page','',0),(24,1,'2014-04-26 05:59:29','2014-04-26 05:59:29','','Hear the Cry: Local','','publish','closed','closed','','hear-the-cry','','','2015-02-17 09:34:14','2015-02-17 17:34:14','',10,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?page_id=24',0,'page','',0),(25,1,'2014-04-26 06:00:05','2014-04-26 06:00:05','','Hear the Cry: Global','','publish','closed','closed','','hear-the-cry-global','','','2015-02-17 09:33:51','2015-02-17 17:33:51','',10,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?page_id=25',0,'page','',0),(26,1,'2014-04-26 06:01:37','2014-04-26 06:01:37','<h1>Missional Community</h1>\r\nMissional Communities are the primary way that we scatter during the week. Meeting in small groups centered around a neighborhood, justice need, or common mission, we pray, eat, and spend time together as we focus on living out Jesus’ teachings.\r\n\r\nEach Missional Community has three identities:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"padding-bottom: .75em;\"><strong>Family</strong>: Missional Communities “do life” together. We share meals, resources, pain, joy, and care for one another as the family of God.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"padding-bottom: .75em;\"><strong>Missionary</strong>: Missional Communities pursue active ways to publicly live out our faith and share the gospel and tangibly embody the kingdom of God in our communities. This is often centered around a common mission (local foster care, a specific business/organization, etc.) or a general neighborhood area.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"padding-bottom: .75em;\"><strong>Disciple: </strong>Missional Communities actively encourage each other in the study of Scripture, learning the teachings of Jesus, becoming more like him, and carrying on his mission in the world.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Missional Community Primer</h2>\r\nThe Missional Community Primer is designed to help <em>new communities</em> form and allow current communities to renew their vision. We encourage everybody to work through the primer as they begin their Missional Community.\r\n\r\n[page_actions]<a href=\"http://ajesuschurch.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/ajc_bt_mc_primer_web.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Missional Community Primer</a> [/page_actions]\r\n<h2>Missional Community Commitment</h2>\r\nThe Missional Community Commitment is designed to help <em>existing communities </em>renew their vision. We encourage everybody to work through the commitments every year.\r\n\r\n[page_actions]<a href=\"http://ajesuschurch.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/ajc_bt_mc_2015-2016_commitment.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Missional Community Commitment</a>[/page_actions]','Missional Community','','publish','closed','closed','','missional-community','','','2016-02-04 12:29:10','2016-02-04 20:29:10','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?page_id=26',0,'page','',0),(28,1,'2014-04-26 06:06:30','2014-04-26 06:06:30','<h1>Basics</h1>\r\nBasics is designed to introduce you to the way Bridgetown steps into its unique place within the family of God. Part one of Basics takes place on two consecutive Sundays and introduces people to Bridgetown’s history, theological distinctives, and the nuts and bolts of Missional Communities. Part two of Basics takes place on four consecutive Wednesday nights to learn hands-on what it looks like to be part of a Missional Community.\r\n\r\nDates: 2 Sundays (October 16 &amp; 23; 2 – 4 PM) and 4 Wednesdays (October 26, Nov 2, 9, &amp; 16; 6:30 – 8:30 PM)\r\n\r\n[page_actions][email address=bridgetownmc@ajesuschurch.org]Contact For More Information[/email][/page_actions]','Basics','','publish','closed','closed','','basics','','','2016-06-20 09:35:17','2016-06-20 17:35:17','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?page_id=28',0,'page','',0),(30,1,'2014-04-26 06:54:16','2014-04-26 06:54:16',' ','','','publish','open','closed','','30','','','2016-07-07 05:19:48','2016-07-07 13:19:48','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?p=30',0,'nav_menu_item','',0),(31,1,'2014-04-26 06:54:16','2014-04-26 06:54:16',' ','','','publish','open','closed','','31','','','2016-07-07 05:19:48','2016-07-07 13:19:48','',10,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?p=31',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(32,1,'2014-04-26 06:54:16','2014-04-26 06:54:16',' ','','','publish','open','closed','','32','','','2016-07-07 05:19:48','2016-07-07 13:19:48','',10,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?p=32',0,'nav_menu_item','',0),(33,1,'2014-04-26 07:17:22','2014-04-26 07:17:22','','Church Planting &amp; Evangelism','','publish','closed','closed','','church-planting','','','2014-07-17 09:42:54','2014-07-17 17:42:54','',10,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?page_id=33',0,'page','',0),(35,1,'2014-04-26 07:20:47','2014-04-26 07:20:47','<h1><strong>The House of Learning</strong></h1>\r\nHouse of Learning equips followers of Jesus  to live life on mission, reach their communities, and to  better understand and interpret Scripture. Below is a selection of classes that we currently offer.\r\n\r\n[page_actions]<a href=\"https://drive.google.com/folderview?id=0By45aTstha2JQnNZdE1KMHRZNTA&amp;usp=sharing\" target=\"_blank\">Bridgetown Class Files</a> [/page_actions]\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h1>God &amp; Money</h1>\r\n[two_third padding=\"0 20px 0 0\"]God &amp; Money is a two week biblically based financial class that teaches what God tells us about managing the blessings he gives us. During this class we will discuss the things of this world that distract and pull us away from God’s plan. We will describe God’s attitude towards providing for our needs and the abundance that we see when we follow his guidance. The goal of this class is to examine God’s plan and work together to apply this to our everyday lives in a way that affects every aspect of your Christian walk.[/two_third]\r\n\r\n[one_third_last]\r\n<strong>New dates for this class coming soon.</strong>[/one_third_last]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h1><strong>Emotionally Healthy Church</strong></h1>\r\n[two_third padding=\"0 20px 0 0\"]In the church, as a general rule, we often teach people how to read the Scriptures, how to pray, how to repent of sin, have faith, do justice, preach the gospel, etc. But we don’t teach people how to navigate emotional pain. How to feel, and to feel well. Over the course of six weeks, the Emotionally Healthy Church class is designed to provide participants with steps to help reshape themselves from the inside out.[/two_third]\r\n\r\n[one_third_last]\r\n<strong>New dates for this class coming soon.</strong>[/one_third_last]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h1><strong>Problem of Evil</strong></h1>\r\n[two_third padding=\"0 20px 0 0\"]The Problem of Evil is a four week class crafted to provide students with a biblical framework for understanding suffering, tragedy, and injustice. Along the way we will examine various theological understandings of the problem of evil as well as how these views have been applied throughout church history. Finally, we will discuss pragmatic ways to understand, process, discuss, and experience the problem of evil in our own lives, and in the lives of those around us.[/two_third]\r\n\r\n[one_third_last]\r\n<strong>New dates for this class coming soon.</strong>[/one_third_last]','House of Learning','','publish','closed','closed','','houseoflearning','','','2016-06-09 10:40:48','2016-06-09 18:40:48','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?page_id=35',0,'page','',0),(36,1,'2014-04-26 07:23:16','2014-04-26 07:23:16','','Church Planting & Evangelism','','publish','open','closed','','36','','','2016-07-07 05:19:48','2016-07-07 13:19:48','',10,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?p=36',0,'nav_menu_item','',0),(37,1,'2014-04-26 08:29:15','2014-04-26 08:29:15',' ','','','publish','open','closed','','37','','','2016-07-07 05:18:49','2016-07-07 13:18:49','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?p=37',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(40,1,'2014-04-26 08:29:15','2014-04-26 08:29:15',' ','','','publish','open','closed','','40','','','2016-07-07 05:18:49','2016-07-07 13:18:49','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?p=40',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),(59,1,'2014-05-12 08:15:14','2014-05-12 08:15:14','','John Mark Comer','','publish','closed','closed','','john-mark-corner','','','2014-05-21 22:27:02','2014-05-21 22:27:02','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=59',1,'speaker','',0),(60,1,'2014-05-12 08:17:55','2014-05-12 08:17:55','','The Beginning','','publish','closed','closed','','the-beginning','','','2014-09-13 08:29:07','2014-09-13 16:29:07','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?post_type=teaching&#038;p=60',257,'teaching','',0),(77,50,'2014-05-15 13:02:13','2014-05-15 21:02:13','','Carry Your Name','','publish','closed','closed','','carry-your-name','','','2016-07-18 04:44:44','2016-07-18 12:44:44','',0,'http://ajesuschurch.org/?post_type=music_release&#038;p=77',1,'music_release','',0),(81,50,'2014-05-15 13:07:04','2014-05-15 20:07:04','By the Bruce Brothers','You Created Me','','draft','closed','closed','','you-created-me','','','2016-07-18 04:29:35','2016-07-18 12:29:35','',0,'http://ajesuschurch.org/?post_type=music_release&#038;p=81',8,'music_release','',0),(84,50,'2014-05-15 13:11:56','2014-05-15 21:11:56','','Gloria','','publish','closed','closed','','gloria','','','2016-07-18 04:45:32','2016-07-18 12:45:32','',0,'http://ajesuschurch.org/?post_type=music_release&#038;p=84',3,'music_release','',0),(86,50,'2014-05-15 13:13:19','2014-05-15 20:13:19','','Synthesis','','draft','closed','closed','','synthesis','','','2016-07-18 04:27:53','2016-07-18 12:27:53','',0,'http://ajesuschurch.org/?post_type=music_release&#038;p=86',6,'music_release','',0),(116,3,'2014-05-21 22:24:07','2014-05-21 22:24:07','','Loveology / Divorce','','publish','closed','closed','','loveology-divorce','','','2014-07-17 09:21:24','2014-07-17 17:21:24','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?post_type=teaching&#038;p=116',273,'teaching','',0),(134,3,'2014-05-28 19:23:44','2014-05-28 19:23:44','<span style=\"color: #303030;\">Unite with other followers of Jesus from all over the Greater Portland Area as we pray and fast for a move of God in our cities.</span>','Seven','','publish','closed','closed','','1401305024','','','2014-09-08 09:58:24','2014-09-08 17:58:24','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?post_type=event&#038;p=134',1,'event','',0),(189,4,'2014-06-11 19:23:28','2014-06-11 19:23:28','','Learning Tile and Vibe','','inherit','open','open','','tile1','','','2014-06-11 19:23:28','2014-06-11 19:23:28','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2014/06/tile1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(191,4,'2014-06-11 19:26:29','2014-06-11 19:26:29','','tile2','','inherit','open','open','','tile2','','','2014-06-11 19:26:29','2014-06-11 19:26:29','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2014/06/tile2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(194,4,'2014-06-11 19:35:42','2014-06-11 19:35:42','','tile4','','inherit','open','open','','tile4','','','2014-06-11 19:35:42','2014-06-11 19:35:42','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2014/06/tile4.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(195,4,'2014-06-11 19:36:05','2014-06-11 19:36:05','','tile5','','inherit','open','open','','tile5','','','2014-06-11 19:36:05','2014-06-11 19:36:05','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2014/06/tile5.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(210,8,'2014-06-15 13:26:50','2014-06-15 20:26:50','<div id=\"block-f0e10aa36b8ef5db705e\" class=\"sqs-block html-block sqs-block-html\" style=\"color: #000000\">\n<div class=\"sqs-block-content\">\n\nAs young people, we set the challenge at the start of this year to read through, soak up, and enjoy the entire story God gave us in the Scriptures; we’re doing this by reading through the <a style=\"color: #000000\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/The-Year-Bible-Premium-Slimline/dp/141431244X/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1398446939&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=one+year+bible+large+print\">One Year Bible</a>.\n\nToday’s reading from Judges is a powerful reminder of the unseen reality we’re a part of as humanity.\n\nReading through the Psalms we’re comforted through a torrent of emotions by those who put into words what all of us at some point in our lives have, are, or will one day experience. A reminder that we’re all in this together.\n\nOne human condition that comes up over and over is <em>fear, </em>or more commonly the result of living in fear; the word <em>afraid.</em>\n\nObjects don’t fear… people do. This word <em>afraid </em>is almost always used in conjunction with <em>people</em> — that is, “he is, or she is, afraid” not “it is afraid”. This is key to understand because whenever we as people experience an emotion, it’s one that Jesus knows well… and for some of us, that’s a point blank reminder to hope, to not give up… He see’s you and knows exactly what you’re going through at this moment.\n\nJudges 4 is the telling of what seems to be an almost mystical story of God interacting with humanity… but why the line? Why do we disconnect and discount that what God did “back then” He’s now unable to do? I beg the response that it’s because we don’t remind ourselves of His love for us. In Jude, there’s a line that says, “…keep yourself in the love of God…”. Wow. That’s where He wants us, constantly reminded of who He is.\n\nGod wants so badly to show the world who He is that He over and over blesses a group of people called the Israelites, in hopes that others would look on and see and want to know that God, but humanity is the loose link in the chain and most of time they choose to come up with ideas and plans of their own and reject this “Creator God’s” design for them.\n\nJudges 4 introduces us to a few people, one of whom is a guy named Sisera, an army commander that ruthlessly oppresses the Israelites. This guy is strong, in-fact the writer makes a point to say that this guy has 900 iron chariots which is to say he’s got everything he needs to tell people what to do and they’ll listen. We also see a lady prophet named Deborah, that is, someone who God speaks to so that she can then communicate that message to a bunch of people. God does just that and gives her a  message to pass onto a guy named Barak. Here’s where it get’s interesting. Barak does what he’s told and gathers 10,000 men to stand up to ‘strong guy Sisera\' and his army. Think about this though, 900 iron chariots doesn’t mean 900 guys fighting, that’s just the tip of the spear… so though Barak has 10,000 men he’s still way outdone by the situation in front of him. But then Deborah says something profound, pulling back the curtain of our visible reality and allowing us a look into what we so often forget about; she says:\n<blockquote style=\"font-style: italic\">“Get ready! This is the day the LORD will give you victory over Sisera, <em><strong style=\"color: #222222\">for the LORD is marching ahead of you</strong></em>.” So Barak led his 10,000 warriors down the slopes of Mount Tabor into battle. When Barak attacked, <em><strong style=\"color: #222222\">the LORD</strong></em> threw Sisera and all his chariots and warriors into a panic.” Judges 4v14-15a</blockquote>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"block-yui_3_10_1_1_1398453631685_36052\" class=\"sqs-block html-block sqs-block-html\" style=\"color: #000000\">\n<div class=\"sqs-block-content\">\n\nThe story ends like you’d expect… they win. But it’s so easy to skip over the core of what just happened yet it’s that very core reality that builds our expectation that it’s <em>God who will save us</em> in the midst of an overwhelming fearful time; when we’re <em>afraid.</em>\n\n<strong style=\"color: #222222\">Keeping ourselves in that love means reminding, and reminding, and reminding, and reminding ourselves of who Jesus is until it becomes our default response when faced with fear.</strong>\n\nHere’s a few statements, verses, that help us stay in that place. If you’re in <em>that</em> place of <em>afraid, </em>play these like tracks on repeat in your head and on your lips today. If you’re fine, and everything is ok then breathe a deep breath of thankfulness, but also humility and know that our lives are fragile — you too will need these reminders at some point; we all will.\n\n<em>When I am afraid, I put my trust in you. In God, whose word I praise — in God I trust and am not afraid…”</em> Psalm 56v3-4a\n\n<em>Whoever dwells in the shelter of the Most High will rest in the shadow of the Almighty. I will say of the Lord, “He is my refuge and my fortress, my God, in whom I trust.”</em> Psalm 91v1-2\n\nSo know today that when you’re <em>afraid</em>, you’re not alone. God is close to you, and it’s because of who He is that we long for more of Him.\n\nHe’s where we run in the <em>afraid </em>times because He loves us; we get to respond by letting Him save us.\n\n</div>\n</div>','\"Afraid\" is not bigger than Jesus.','','trash','closed','closed','','afraid-is-not-bigger-than-jesus__trashed','','','2016-07-18 22:30:11','2016-07-19 06:30:11','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?p=210',0,'post','',0),(214,1,'2014-06-18 01:40:32','2014-06-18 01:40:32','','default-avatar','','inherit','open','open','','default-avatar','','','2014-06-18 01:40:32','2014-06-18 01:40:32','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2014/06/default-avatar.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(261,4,'2014-06-29 22:28:14','2014-06-29 22:28:14','','ajc_web_ws_thumb_htc','','inherit','open','open','','ajc_web_ws_thumb_htc','','','2014-06-29 22:28:14','2014-06-29 22:28:14','',25,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2014/04/ajc_web_ws_thumb_htc.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(293,50,'2014-07-28 12:27:12','2014-07-28 19:27:12','','Carry Your Name EP','','publish','closed','closed','','carry-your-name-ep','','','2016-07-18 04:45:08','2016-07-18 12:45:08','',0,'http://ajesuschurch.org/?post_type=music_release&#038;p=293',2,'music_release','',0),(294,4,'2014-07-16 08:24:57','2014-07-16 16:24:57','','ajc_web_thumb','','inherit','open','open','','ajc_web_thumb','','','2014-07-16 08:24:57','2014-07-16 16:24:57','',4,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2014/03/ajc_web_thumb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(296,4,'2014-07-16 08:26:50','2014-07-16 16:26:50','','ajc_web_thumb','','inherit','open','open','','ajc_web_thumb-2','','','2014-07-16 08:26:50','2014-07-16 16:26:50','',4,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2014/03/ajc_web_thumb1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(305,4,'2014-07-16 13:03:26','2014-07-16 21:03:26','','ajc_web_thumb_2','','inherit','open','open','','ajc_web_thumb_2','','','2014-07-16 13:03:26','2014-07-16 21:03:26','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2014/07/ajc_web_thumb_2.jpg',0,'attachment','i