'ajc_web_thumb_19','','','2014-07-31 12:55:48','2014-07-31 20:55:48','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2014/07/ajc_web_thumb_19.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(520,4,'2014-07-31 13:22:08','2014-07-31 21:22:08','','IMG_8284','','inherit','open','open','','img_8284','','','2014-07-31 13:22:08','2014-07-31 21:22:08','',4,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2014/03/IMG_8284.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(524,4,'2014-07-31 13:50:54','2014-07-31 21:50:54','','IMG_6343','','inherit','open','open','','img_6343','','','2014-07-31 13:50:54','2014-07-31 21:50:54','',4,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2014/03/IMG_6343.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(527,4,'2014-07-31 13:56:39','2014-07-31 21:56:39','','portlandboatandrailroad','','inherit','open','open','','portlandboatandrailroad','','','2014-07-31 13:56:39','2014-07-31 21:56:39','',4,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2014/03/portlandboatandrailroad.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(528,4,'2014-07-31 13:56:54','2014-07-31 21:56:54','','portlandboatandrailroad','','inherit','open','open','','portlandboatandrailroad-2','','','2014-07-31 13:56:54','2014-07-31 21:56:54','',4,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2014/03/portlandboatandrailroad1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(533,4,'2014-08-10 15:53:16','2014-08-10 23:53:16','','ajc_web_hero_11','','inherit','open','open','','ajc_web_hero_11','','','2014-08-10 15:53:16','2014-08-10 23:53:16','',10,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2014/04/ajc_web_hero_11.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(535,4,'2014-08-10 15:54:46','2014-08-10 23:54:46','','ajc_web_hero_11','','inherit','open','open','','ajc_web_hero_11-2','','','2014-08-10 15:54:46','2014-08-10 23:54:46','',10,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2014/04/ajc_web_hero_111.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(536,20,'2014-10-13 11:22:26','2014-10-13 18:22:26','<p class=\"p1\">Whether you have been meeting consistently with a group of people who have yet to get on board with a “mission,” or are just now deciding to start a Missional Community, having a <em>mission</em> is essential to being a <em>missional</em> community.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><i>Duh.</i></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">That’s a pretty easy point that we all get. What gets some of us stuck though is the question, “<em>how do we decide on a mission</em>?”</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">A mission gives the group a purpose, a reason for getting together, a reason for serving together, a reason for sacrificing together. Ultimately, we know that the mission has got to be the Matthew 28 mission—making disciples—but we also have to nail down what that means specifically for your Missional Community. A clear mission provides focus and pushes away distraction. A clear mission inspires, stirs the imagination, and gets people excited.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">For many, the answer could simply be your neighborhood or your office. If your missional community is made up of people from within the same neighborhood or same office building, the answer could very well simply be a mission to your neighbors or coworkers. It doesn’t have to be more complicated than that. For others of us, we might not be connected purely geographically, in the same neighborhood, but are instead linked together by schedule, interests or networks.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">How do we then develop a clear mission?</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><b>It starts with prayer.</b> Ask God where he wants to send you and your community</li>\r\n	<li><b>Reflect on what God has given you and where you are</b>. God has given you and your missional community a unique set of gifts, passions, desires, relationships, and you all live in specific geographical locations.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Use your imagination.</b> Dream about creative ways you can introduce people to King Jesus and his Kingdom. If it hasn’t been done before, that\'s okay. If you could invent the future, what would it be like?</li>\r\n	<li><b>Partner with what others have started.</b> If you can’t think of new ways to change the world, that’s okay too! There are plenty of people out there who are looking for servant-hearted, loving people to help out.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Ask for input.</b> 10 people or 20 people brainstorming together create more ideas than 1 or 2 people.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Step out and decide.</b> Part of leadership is decision making. If you’ve gathered the information, received the input, and done the analysis, go!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Nothing revolutionary, but I hope these 6 tips can be a helpful tool in developing a clear mission for your missional community.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\"><em>Written by: Matt Karsh, Missional Community Director, Sunset: A Jesus Church </em></p>','How do we decide on a mission?','','publish','closed','closed','','how-do-we-decide-on-a-mission','','','2016-07-19 05:43:15','2016-07-19 13:43:15','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?p=536',0,'post','',0),(537,4,'2014-08-10 15:56:01','2014-08-10 23:56:01','','ajc_web_hero_11','','inherit','open','open','','ajc_web_hero_11-3','','','2014-08-10 15:56:01','2014-08-10 23:56:01','',10,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2014/04/ajc_web_hero_112.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(540,4,'2014-08-11 14:58:32','2014-08-11 22:58:32','','ajc_web_thumb_26','','inherit','open','open','','ajc_web_thumb_26','','','2014-08-11 14:58:32','2014-08-11 22:58:32','',35,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2014/04/ajc_web_thumb_26.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(546,4,'2014-08-12 08:57:24','2014-08-12 16:57:24','','ajc_web_hero_17','','inherit','open','open','','ajc_web_hero_17','','','2014-08-12 08:57:24','2014-08-12 16:57:24','',9,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2014/04/ajc_web_hero_17.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(548,4,'2014-08-12 09:16:40','2014-08-1