ine.com/?post_type=staff_member&#038;p=750',5,'staff_member','',0),(751,4,'2014-10-29 16:06:31','2014-10-30 00:06:31','','ajc_staff_matt_norman','','inherit','open','open','','ajc_staff_matt_norman','','','2014-10-29 16:06:31','2014-10-30 00:06:31','',750,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2014/10/ajc_staff_matt_norman.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(755,22,'2014-12-08 09:00:23','2014-12-08 17:00:23','This year for our Hear the Cry giving catalogue, we are putting a huge focus on child/student sponsorship. For many of the countries we work in our primary focus is on children. Food, shelter, family, and the love of Jesus is provided from incredible people that serve these kids day in and day out. One of the main things that we can offer these vulnerable kids is a future, and the best way we can provide for their future is good, consistent education. While providing a good home is a huge step for many of these kids that have had nothing, it is not enough to ensure a healthy future for them and their families. Many of these children have grown up on the streets of Zimbabwe, Somalia, Uganda, India and more. Education, starting with a good foundation in primary school and high school, and then on to college is critical.\r\n\r\nWe have a number of ways you can get involved with children from all over the world providing them with the necessary tools to thrive in their environment. Take a look at all the different options below and hopefully as a church we can take care of hundreds of children and students and provide an opportunity that otherwise would not be possible. <strong>We\'ll be highlighting each organization we work with here on the blog throughout the holiday season. Each blog will feature practical ways to get involved and to contribute financially.</strong>\r\n\r\nYou should know that all of these organizations I have been working with for years, and we have been on the ground working side by side with the locals that care for these kids. I can say with confidence that they are all worthy of our gifts and support and all are current partners of Hear the Cry. If you have any questions please don\'t hesitate to email me or just come on a trip next year and see what God is doing through your generosity. On behalf of the Pastors and Elders we want to say thank you so much for your generosity. All of this is possible because of how you give. May Jesus continue to move his kingdom forward and may we as a church run towards helping the least of these in some of the most vulnerable places on earth.\r\n\r\nGrace &amp; Peace,\r\n\r\nMichael McDonald / Hear the Cry\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Visit each of Hear The Cry\'s partnering organizations:</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://www.thesenumbers.org/impact-circle\" target=\"_blank\">These Numbers Have Faces</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"https://remembernhu.org/give.html\" target=\"_blank\">Remember Nhu</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"https://restoreinternational.org/shop/products/ugandasafehouse/\" target=\"_blank\">Restore International: Girls Safe House</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"https://restoreinternational.org/shop/products/engagesomalia/\" target=\"_blank\">Restore International: Engage Somalia</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"https://restoreinternational.org/shop/products/restore-iraq-refugee-support/\" target=\"_blank\">Restore International: Refugee Iraq</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"https://restoreinternational.org/shop/products/engageiraq/\" target=\"_blank\">Sponsor a Child in Iraq</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://indiahappyhome.org/sponsor-a-child/\" target=\"_blank\">Happy Home for the Handicapped</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://www.lovingheartsbabies.com/#/home\" target=\"_blank\">Loving Hearts Baby Home</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://flyfishingcollaborative.org/give/\" target=\"_blank\">Nicaragua Fish Farm</a> </strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Hea