\"color: #222222;\"></div>\r\n<div style=\"color: #222222;\"></div>\r\n<div style=\"color: #222222;\"></div>\r\n<div style=\"color: #222222;\"></div>\r\n<div style=\"color: #222222;\"></div>\r\n<div style=\"color: #222222;\"></div>','Receive The Holy Spirit: Recommended Reading','','publish','closed','closed','','receive-the-holy-spirit-recommended-reading','','','2016-07-19 03:02:54','2016-07-19 11:02:54','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?p=889',0,'post','',0),(890,4,'2015-02-11 21:09:00','2015-02-12 05:09:00','','Mount_Sinai_BW_3','','inherit','open','open','','mount_sinai_bw_3-2','','','2015-02-11 21:09:00','2015-02-12 05:09:00','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2015/02/Mount_Sinai_BW_31.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(891,4,'2015-02-11 23:03:35','2015-02-12 07:03:35','','ajc_poe12_tile','','inherit','open','open','','ajc_poe12_tile','','','2015-02-11 23:03:35','2015-02-12 07:03:35','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2015/02/ajc_poe12_tile.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(892,4,'2015-02-11 23:04:57','2015-02-12 07:04:57','','ajc_poe12_hero','','inherit','open','open','','ajc_poe12_hero','','','2015-02-11 23:04:57','2015-02-12 07:04:57','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2015/02/ajc_poe12_hero.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(893,4,'2015-02-12 11:20:36','2015-02-12 19:20:36','','ajc_web_thumb_21','','inherit','open','open','','ajc_web_thumb_21','','','2015-02-12 11:20:36','2015-02-12 19:20:36','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2015/02/ajc_web_thumb_21.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(895,6,'2015-02-12 14:17:52','2015-02-12 22:17:52','A time for the Women of Bridgetown to gather for a night of prayer for each other, their families, the church, and the world. Snacks, coffee and other beverages will be provided.','Women\'s Night of Prayer','','publish','closed','closed','','1423779472','','','2015-03-10 08:36:44','2015-03-10 16:36:44','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?post_type=event&#038;p=895',0,'event','',0),(903,4,'2015-02-12 15:13:39','2015-02-12 23:13:39','<h1>About Bridgetown: A Jesus Church</h1>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nWe believe the Church is not another sub-culture, but the making of a new humanity. Its not a building or a weekend activity, but a people. We strive to live out the Gospel in our city throughout the week, then gather each weekend as a collection of Missional Communities. We want to partner with God in his relentless pursuit to put the world to rights. Our prayer is as Jesus prayed, that God’s will would be done in Portland as it is in Heaven.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h1>Doctrinal Primer</h1>\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\">We believe in the life, death, burial, and resurrection of Jesus, and are committed to living out his teachings in the world. As a church family, we feel most closely aligned to the beliefs outlined in The Lausanne Covenant. Our blog is a place where we further explore and discuss doctrine and theology.</span>\r\n\r\n[page_actions]<a href=\"http://ajesuschurch.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/TheLausanneCovenant.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Lausanne Covenant</a> [/page_actions]','About','','publish','closed','closed','','about','','','2015-09-16 20:18:46','2015-09-17 04:18:46','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?page_id=903',0,'page','',0),(905,16,'2015-01-05 09:00:16','2015-01-05 17:00:16','I like reading. I read good. Goodly. I spelle goodly, too. But I hate it when you\'re reading and you come across the expression, “one thing led to another.” What kind of lazy writing is that? Isn\'t it <em>the</em> job of the writer to tell me how <em>this</em> led to <em>that</em>? You can’t just throw that in there!\n\n\"Adolf Hitler was rejected as a young man on his application to art school... One thing led to another... And the United States dropped two atomic bombs on the sovereign nation of Japan.\"\n\nWow! This is some article!\n\nWe laugh, or scratch our head, because we all recognize most things don’t <em>just</em> <em>happen.</em> Take a good marriage for example. It’s doesn’t go, “He saw her, she saw him, they spoke, one-thing-led-to-another, and they lived happily ever after.”\n\nEverybody with a pulse knows there is a huge back-story here. Days, months, years of overcoming challenges, of working through mistakes, of giving and forgiving, of caring, growing, building, sharing, celebrating… years of life! It’s broken down into single moments, choices, and words. Tie them together, and that’s how one thing leads to another. It’s simple math (just my speed) and each moment counts, like each word we speak to one another. Imagine how our marriage story might rise with more of the right heart and the right conversations.\n<h3>My father-in-law often said, <em>“words mean things.”</em> They do. They can hurt or heal us, deflate or inspire us, condemn or bless us. Paul said, <em>“Let nothing inappropriate or unkind leave your mouth. Instead, offer words that build up and impart grace to those who hear it.”</em> The Message translation concludes Ephesians 4:29 like this, <em>“Each word a gift.”</em></h3>\nToday, give the gift of words to your spouse. As a prompt, here is a “starter-list” of things you might deftly slip into daily conversation, or send in a text, or write on a note that you hide in a dresser drawer. However you do it, and whatever you choose to say, give it a try, and see how “one thing leads to another.”\n\nYou are wonderful.\n\nThat was really great.\n\nWhat’s on your mind today?\n\nI’m glad we had that time together.\n\nIs there anything I can do to help?\n\nLet me just listen.\n\nLet’s go to the mall together and I’ll hold your purse while you shop. (not!)\n\nI am so thankful I married you!\n\nI appreciate all the things you’ve done for me.\n\nI missed you today.\n\nI was wrong.\n\nI’m sorry.\n\nPlease forgive me.\n\nI love you.\n\nWould you pray for me?\n\nI’m praying for you today.\n\nI love to see your eyes sparkle when you smile.\n\nThat took a lot of thought to do.\n\nYou make every day brighter.\n\nAs always, you look amazing today.\n\nI really trust you.\n\nThank you for loving me.\n\nI can always count on you.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;','Sticks and Stones Marriage','','trash','closed','closed','','sticks-and-stones-marriage__trashed','','','2016-07-18 22:29:31','2016-07-19 06:29:31','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?p=905',0,'post','',0),(907,4,'2015-02-19 14:05:09','2015-02-19 22:05:09','','ajc_firstcorinthians_hero','','inherit','open','open','','ajc_firstcorinthians_hero','','','2015-02-19 14:05:09','2015-02-19 22:05:09','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2015/02/ajc_firstcorinthians_hero.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(908,4,'2015-02-19 14:05:21','2015-02-19 22:05:21','','ajc_firstcorinthians_tile','','inherit','open','open','','ajc_firstcorinthians_tile','','','2015-02-19 14:05:21','2015-02-19 22:05:21','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2015/02/ajc_firstcorinthians_tile.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(909,4,'2015-02-19 14:21:28','2015-02-19 22:21:28','','I am Paul','','publish','closed','closed','','i-am-paul','','','2015-02-19 14:24:56','2015-02-19 22:24:56','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?post_type=teaching&#038;p=909',119,'teaching','',0),(910,4,'2015-02-19 14:23:31','2015-02-19 22:23:31','','ajc_firstcorinthians_tile','','inherit','open','open','','ajc_firstcorinthians_tile-2','','','2015-02-19 14:23:31','2015-02-19 22:23:31','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2015/02/ajc_firstcorinthians_tile1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(911,4,'2015-02-19 14:33:24','2015-02-19 22:33:24','','To The Church of God in Corinth...','','publish','closed','closed','','to-the-church-of-god-in-corinth','','','2015-02-19 14:33:24','2015-02-19 22:33:24','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?post_type=teaching&#038;p=911',118,'teaching','',0),(912,4,'2015-02-19 14:37:16','2015