'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?post_type=teaching&#038;p=1373',43,'teaching','',0),(1374,4,'2015-10-20 10:49:45','2015-10-20 18:49:45','','ajc_bt_gardencity_hero','','inherit','open','open','','ajc_bt_gardencity_hero','','','2015-10-20 10:49:45','2015-10-20 18:49:45','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2015/10/ajc_bt_gardencity_hero.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1375,4,'2015-10-20 10:49:55','2015-10-20 18:49:55','','ajc_bt_gardencity_tile','','inherit','open','open','','ajc_bt_gardencity_tile','','','2015-10-20 10:49:55','2015-10-20 18:49:55','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2015/10/ajc_bt_gardencity_tile.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1376,42,'2015-06-15 10:43:10','2015-06-15 17:43:10','Papa,\r\n\r\nThank you for pouring your love over the people of Beaverton.\r\n\r\nYou saw us as we were being formed.\r\n\r\nYou are both ahead of us and behind us. There is no lonely space. What a difficult thing to accept… help us believe. For us who do, help us go deeper. For us who don’t, meet us in our longing.\r\n\r\nYou know when we wake up and when we fall asleep. You’re close to us, even when our minds, emotions, and senses scream otherwise. Adjust our senses to parallel yours, Father.\r\n\r\nYou see each corner, each bus stop, each park, and every inch of sidewalk. There is no hidden space.\r\n\r\nYou see the kids who walk to school on Lombard, on Scholls, and on every other street in this place we call home. And you are with them.\r\n\r\nYou see us who frantically getting ready as the sun comes up. Be with us as we work at Nike, Intel, Starbucks, McDonalds, Washington Square, Cedar Hills Crossing, or any other work space in our city.\r\n\r\nYou see us who don’t have jobs right now… and you call us beloved.\r\n\r\nYou see us who put on our work clothes and cut grass, bushes, and trees until dark.\r\n\r\nYou see us who have degrees, and us who don’t.\r\n\r\nYou see us who can afford groceries, and us who can’t right now. We ask, “please provide.\"\r\n\r\nYou see us moms, dads, uncles, aunts, grandmas, grandpas, foster parents, and friends, as we rush around doing our best to get our kids off to one of the forty-six schools in our area. You know each one of the 38,500 students as if they were the only one that existed.\r\n\r\nYou call us your favorite, your bride, your church.\r\n\r\nOpen up our lives to grasp and experience more to your heart, Papa.\r\n\r\nThank you for caring when it feels like no one else does.\r\n\r\nTell us again, we who find ourselves in this place called Beaverton, what your thoughts are about us.\r\n\r\nWe pray that God\'s will would be done in Beaverton as it is in Heaven.\r\n\r\nAmen.','A Prayer for Beaverton','','publish','closed','closed','','a-prayer-for-beaverton','','','2016-07-19 00:28:55','2016-07-19 08:28:55','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/?p=1376',0,'post','',0),(1377,4,'2015-10-22 15:20:41','2015-10-22 23:20:41','','ajc_bt_sweatshop_hero_','','inherit','open','open','','ajc_bt_sweatshop_hero_-3','','','2015-10-22 15:20:41','2015-10-22 23:20:41','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2015/10/ajc_bt_sweatshop_hero_.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1378,4,'2015-10-22 15:20:52','2015-10-22 23:20:52','','ajc_bt_sweatshop_tile_','','inherit','open','open','','ajc_bt_sweatshop_tile_-3','','','2015-10-22 15:20:52','2015-10-22 23:20:52','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2015/10/ajc_bt_sweatshop_tile_.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1379,4,'2015-10-25 10:05:09','2015-10-25 18:05:09','','ajc_bt_gardencity_hero','','inherit','open','open','','ajc_bt_gardencity_hero-2','','','2015-10-25 10:05:09','2015-10-25 18:05:09','',0,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2015/10/ajc_bt_gardencity_hero1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1380,4,'2015-10-25 10:05:27','2015-10-25 18:05:27','','ajc_bt_gardencity_tile','','inherit','open','open','','ajc_bt_gardenc