30\" /></a>\r\n<h8>Generous Justice</h8>\r\n<h9>by Tim Keller\r\nThe best overview of a theology of justice we’ve ever read put together in a short, easy to read book.</h9>\r\n\r\n[/one_third][one_third padding=\"0 25px 0 0\"]\r\n\r\n<a target=\"blank\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1587433605/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=9325&creativeASIN=1587433605&linkCode=as2&tag=briajeschu-20&linkId=7XG5J776EU7SWGYI\"><img src=\"http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2016/01/kingdom_conspiracy.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"825\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1940\" /></a>\r\n<h8>Kingdom Conspiracy</h8>\r\n<h9>by Scott McNight\r\nA scripturally rich and spiritually compelling vision of the kingdom.</h9>\r\n\r\n[/one_third][one_third_last padding=\"0 25px 0 0\"]\r\n\r\n<a target=\"blank\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0310520754/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=9325&creativeASIN=0310520754&linkCode=as2&tag=briajeschu-20&linkId=T4BYSWJDTPQ7VB4K\"><img src=\"http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2016/01/emotionally_healthy_church1.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"825\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1946\" /></a>\r\n<h8>The Emotionally Healthy Church</h8>\r\n<h9>by Peter Scazzaro\r\nOutside of the Bible, no other book has had a greater impact on Bridgetown’s cultural ethos.</h9>\r\n\r\n[/one_third_last]\r\n[one_third padding=\"0 25px 0 0\"]\r\n\r\n<a target=\"blank\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0802867618/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=9325&creativeASIN=0802867618&linkCode=as2&tag=briajeschu-20&linkId=HK67MCVZKAGQQ26P \"><img src=\"http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2016/01/how_not_to_be.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"825\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1944\" /></a>\r\n<h8>How (Not) To Be Secular</h8>\r\n<h9>by James K. A. Smith\r\nA short synopsis of the seminal work on secularism by sociologist Charles Taylor.</h9>\r\n\r\n[/one_third][one_third pa