creativeASIN=0310721636&linkCode=as2&tag=briajeschu-20&linkId=W7UWWWNDQCW4YJMZ \"><img src=\"http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2016/01/heart_sing.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"825\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1905\" /></a>\r\n<h8>Thoughts To Make Your Heart Sing</h8>\r\n<h9>by Sally Lloyd-Jones\r\nProfound truths from the Bible told in a conversational tone. Ages 3+.</h9>\r\n\r\n[/one_third][one_third_last padding=\"0 25px 0 0\"]\r\n\r\n<a target=\"blank\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0768427398/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=9325&creativeASIN=0768427398&linkCode=as2&tag=briajeschu-20&linkId=RK7JVFQZ6E34IA44\"><img src=\"http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2016/01/kids_on_purpose.jpg\" width=\"600\" height=\"825\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1915\" /></a>\r\n<h8>Loving Your Kids On Purpose</h8>\r\n<h9>by Danny Silk\r\nHow to raise your children to be people who choose God.</h9>\r\n\r\n[/one_third_last]','Bookstore','','inherit','open','open','','1877-revision-v1','','','2016-06-09 10:36:14','2016-06-09 18:36:14','',1877,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/1877-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(2360,37,'2016-06-09 10:40:10','2016-06-09 18:40:10','<h1><strong>The House of Learning</strong></h1>\r\nHouse of Learning equips followers of Jesus  to live life on mission, reach their communities, and to  better understand and interpret Scripture. Below is a selection of classes that we currently offer.\r\n\r\n[page_actions]<a href=\"https://drive.google.com/folderview?id=0By45aTstha2JQnNZdE1KMHRZNTA&amp;usp=sharing\" target=\"_blank\">Bridgetown Class Files</a> [/page_actions]\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h1>God &amp; Money</h1>\r\n[two_third padding=\"0 20px 0 0\"]God &amp; Money is a two week biblically based financial class that teaches what God tells us about managing the blessings he gives us. During this class we will discuss the things of this world that distract and pull us away from God’s plan. We will describe God’s attitude towards providing for our needs and the abundance that we see when we follow his guidance. The goal of this class is to examine God’s plan and work together to apply this to our everyday lives in a way that affects every aspect of your Christian walk.[/two_third]\r\n\r\n[one_third_last]\r\nNew dates for this class coming soon.[/one_third_last]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h1><strong>Emotionally Healthy Church</strong></h1>\r\n[two_third padding=\"0 20px 0 0\"]In the church, as a general rule, we often teach people how to read the Scriptures, how to pray, how to repent of sin, have faith, do justice, preach the gospel, etc. But we don’t teach people how to navigate emotional pain. How to feel, and to feel well. Over the course of six weeks, the Emotionally Healthy Church class is designed to provide participants with steps to help reshape themselves from the inside out.[/two_third]\r\n\r\n[one_third_last]\r\nNew dates for this class coming soon.[/one_third_last]\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h1><strong>Problem of Evil</strong></h1>\r\n[two_third padding=\"0 20px 0 0\"]The Problem of Evil is a four week class crafted to provide students with a biblical framework for understanding suffering, tragedy, and injustice. Along the way we will examine various theological understandings of the problem of evil as well as how these views have been applied throughout church history. Finally, we will discuss pragmatic ways to understand, process, discuss, and experience the problem of evil in our own lives, and in the lives of those around us.[/two_third]\r\n\r\n[one_third_last]\r\nNew dates for this class coming soon.[/one_third_last]','House of Learning','','inherit','open','open','','35-revision-v1','','','2016-06-09 10:40:10','2016-06-09 18:40:10','',35,'http://bridgetown.wpengine.com/35-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(2361,37,'2016-06-09 10:40:48','2016-06-09 18:40:48','<h1><strong>The House of Learning</strong></h1>\r\nHouse of Learning equips followers of Jesus  to live life on mission, reach their communities, and to  better understand and interpret Scripture. Below is a selection of classes that we currently offer.\r\n\r\n[page_actions]<a href=\"https://drive.google.com/folderview?id=0By45aTstha2JQnNZdE1KMHRZNTA&amp;usp=sharing\" target=\"_blank\">Bridgetown Class Files</a> [/page_actions]\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h1>God &amp; Money</h1>\r\n[two_third padding=\"0 20px 0 0\"]God &amp; Money is a two week biblically based financial class that teaches what God tells us about managing the blessings he gives us. During this class we will discuss the things of this world that distract and pull us away from God’s plan. We will describe God’s attitude towards providing for our needs and the abundance that we see when we follow his guidance. The goal of this class is to examine God’s plan and work together to apply this to our everyday lives in a way that affects every aspect of your Christian walk.[/two_third]\r\n\r\n[one_third_last]\r\n<strong>New dates for this class coming soon.</strong>[/one_third_last]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h1><strong>Emotionally Healthy Church</strong></h1>\r\n[two_third padding=\"0 20px 0 0\"]In the church, as a general rule, we often teach people how to read the Scriptures, how to pray, how to repent of sin, have faith, do justice, preach the gospel, etc. But we don’t teach people how to navigate emotional pain. How to feel, and to feel well. Over the course of six weeks, the Emotionally Healthy Church class is designed to provide participants with steps to help reshape themselves from the inside out.[/two_third]\r\n\r\n[one_third_last]\r\n<strong>New dates for this class coming soon.</strong>[/one_third_last]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h1><strong>Problem of Evil</strong></h1>\r\n[two_third padding=\"0 20px 0 0\"]The Problem of Evil is a four week class crafted to provide students with a biblical framework for understanding suffering, tragedy, and injustice. Alo